message:
this exception appears when using JNI with linux ( C# dll in java application) 
/usr/java/packages/lib/amd64/SharpAuthenticator.dll: /usr/java/packages/lib/amd64/SharpAuthenticator.dll: invalid ELF header (Possible cause: endianness mismatch)

/usr/java/packages/lib/amd64/cppAuthenticator.dll: /usr/java/packages/lib/amd64/cppAuthenticator.dll: invalid ELF header (Possible cause: endianness mismatch)

however its working well on windows 

i installed wine on linux for .net framework 

can anyone help ?

data.message: NO, wine on Linux is limited to a few basic programs. If you want .NET on Linux go for ASP.NET core
